                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Why Are CRT TV Screens So Hard to Photograph?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/why-are-crt-tv-screens-so-hard-to-photograph/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/07/star-trek-deep-space-9-on-a-crt-tv.jpg" length="310" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[TVs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Monitors]]></category><category><![CDATA[photography]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Discover the surprising reason behind CRT screens' elusive nature in photos and videos.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you're deep in the CRT hobby like I am now, you've probably realized that when you try to share your hobby online, your screens don't quite look right on camera. This is nothing new, and happens because of the fundamental way CRTs work.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 22:00:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/why-are-crt-tv-screens-so-hard-to-photograph/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How to Turn Off Annoying AI Features on Your Google Pixel Phone]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/how-to-turn-off-annoying-ai-features-google-pixel-phone/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aman Kumar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/robot_hands_reaching_for_a_google_pixel_smartphone_surrounded_by_red_warning_icons_with_exclamation_marks.png" length="1289" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel 10]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google]]></category><category><![CDATA[ai]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Get rid of unwanted AI features from your Pixel.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>One of the major selling points of the Pixel phones is their AI features. However, I'm not a big fan of AI features on a smartphone. If you're like me, then keep reading to find out how to turn off all the annoying AI features on your Google Pixel phone.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 21:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/how-to-turn-off-annoying-ai-features-google-pixel-phone/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Can You Really Hear the Difference Between Lossless and Lossy Compressed Audio?]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/can-you-really-hear-the-difference-between-lossless-and-lossy-compressed-audio/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/a-smartphone-with-headphones-and-an-app-being-opened.png" length="2033" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[Spotify]]></category><category><![CDATA[Audio]]></category><category><![CDATA[headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[Speakers]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Ditching lossless audio might be no loss at all.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>With lossless audio coming to Spotify Premium, this high-fidelity audio option is now available to most music streaming subscribers on big services. That's great in principle, but is it worth sacrificing your bandwidth, storage space, and paying a premium to have access to lossless media?</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 20:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/can-you-really-hear-the-difference-between-lossless-and-lossy-compressed-audio/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Keycap Shape Matters More To Your Keyboard Than You Think]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/keycap-shape-matters-more-to-your-keyboard-than-you-think/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/10/rsz_img20251007134249_01.png" length="2475" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mechanical Keyboards]]></category><category><![CDATA[Keyboards]]></category><category><![CDATA[DIY]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            A good keyboard starts with the shape of your keycaps.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you're customizing your mechanical keyboard with aftermarket keycaps, it helps to understand their shapes (aka keycap profiles) so that you can pick the right ones. Here’s a quick crash course on everything you need to know about keycap profiles.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 19:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/keycap-shape-matters-more-to-your-keyboard-than-you-think/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[You're Using This Powerful Tech Constantly and Didn't Know It]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/what-is-optical-character-recognition-ocr/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Patrick Campanale]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/10/person-holding-a-document-while-scanning-text-with-a-smartphone-highlighted-by-a-red-scanning-overlay.png" length="1232" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[OneDrive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Camera]]></category><category><![CDATA[iPhone]]></category><category><![CDATA[Adobe]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Extracting text from pictures has never been easier. 
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Have you ever seen the term “optical character recognition” or OCR and wondered what it meant? Well, I’m here to help you understand what OCR is. It’s very possible that you’ve used OCR and didn’t know it. You might have even used it today. Here’s everything you need to know about optical character recognition.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 18:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/what-is-optical-character-recognition-ocr/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[8 Smartphone Habits You Should Probably Stop Doing]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/smartphone-habits-you-should-stop/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Kabir Jain]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/hand-holding-a-smartphone-with-a-battery-charge-notification.jpg" length="1073" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[batteries]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Some of these "pro tips" belong in a museum.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>We’ve all picked up weird habits with our phones over the years. Little routines that made sense at the time, passed down like tech folklore. “Close your apps to save battery.” “Never charge overnight.” “Let your battery hit zero before plugging it in.”</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 18:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/smartphone-habits-you-should-stop/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[TVs Might Be Getting Too Bright Now]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/tvs-might-be-getting-too-bright-now/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/shutterstock_2688877421.jpg" length="317" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[TVs]]></category><category><![CDATA[Monitors]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Don't walk towards the light!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The arrival of HDR was a revelation, and for a long time TVs struggled to reach the brightness needed to make this new video standard shine, but now thanks to a relentless brightness war, even entry-level TVs can reach heights only high-end sets could dream of before.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 17:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/tvs-might-be-getting-too-bright-now/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The Best VPNs for Android in 2025]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/best-vpns-for-android/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Kris Henges]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2025/09/pixel-10-pro-xl-camera-lens.jpg" length="1046" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[buying guide]]></category><category><![CDATA[VPN]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Browse privately on your Android phone with the help of a VPN.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Android phones and tablets are at just as much risk as any other device for snooping, surveillance, and cybercrime. To help you combat these dangers, we’ve put together the best VPNs for Android so you can surf more securely.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 17:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/best-vpns-for-android/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[The End of Steam on Chromebooks Is a Tragedy]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/the-end-of-steam-on-chromebooks-is-a-tragedy/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/a-chromebook-with-steam-open-with-the-steam-logo-and-the-chrome-logo-next-to-it.png" length="2774" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Chromebook & Chrome OS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Steam]]></category><category><![CDATA[GeForce Now]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Play Store]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The clock is ticking for Steam on Chromebooks...
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>On the first day of 2026, the Steam Beta for Chromebooks will end. This means you will no longer have the option to play Steam games on your Chromebook with official support. If you're not a Chromebook user, this might not sound like much of an issue. After all, who plays video games on a Chromebook?</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 16:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/the-end-of-steam-on-chromebooks-is-a-tragedy/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[5 Pocket Alternatives That Can Replace the Now-Defunct "Read It Later" Service]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/pocket-alternatives/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[T.M. Amrita]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/mozilla-pocket-logo-on-a-red-background.jpg" length="43" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mozilla]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[App Store]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Play Store]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Save and read articles later with these apps.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>One of the most famous read-later apps, Pocket by Mozilla, shut down permanently in October. The app was known for its ease of use, sync, and interface, leaving many loyal users shifting to similar apps.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 11 Oct 2025 15:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/pocket-alternatives/</guid></item></channel>
